## EXPLORATION REPORT: LearnMoreRewardProgram Screen

### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE & FILES

**Location:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/rnm-app-fintech-rewardprogram/src/screens/LearnMoreRewardProgram/`

**Files:**
- `index.tsx` (145 lines) - Logic hook with state & tracking
- `view.tsx` (40 lines) - Presentational component
- `Models/index.ts` (17 lines) - TypeScript interfaces

---

### 2. COMPLETE FILE CONTENTS

#### **index.tsx (Hook/Logic Component)**
```typescript
import {
  useFocusEffect,
  useNavigation,
  useRoute,
} from '@react-navigation/native';
import { propsItems } from '@semparar/design-system-app/src/atomic/organisms/Accordion/Models';
import {
  MARGIN_STANDING_XS,
  PADDING_INNER_LARGER,
} from '@semparar/design-system-app/src/settings/environment';
import React, { useCallback, useMemo, useRef } from 'react';
import { useWindowDimensions } from 'react-native';
import { eventScreenViewV3, eventSelectContent } from '~/constants/functions';
import { useRootStore } from '~/store';
import ApiError from '../../atomic/organisms/ApiError';
import { useScreenViewTracking } from '../../hooks/tracking';
import {
  ParameterPointsProgramStatus,
  ParameterPointsProgramValue,
} from '../../services/models';
import { sanitizeTaxonomy } from '../../utils/functions';
import type { UseLearnMoreRewardProgramReturn } from './Models';
import LearnMoreRewardProgramView from './view';

function useLearnMoreRewardProgram(): UseLearnMoreRewardProgramReturn {
  const route = useRoute();
  const navigation = useNavigation();
  const hasFocused = useRef(false);
  const { width } = useWindowDimensions();
  const { status, selectedCategory } = useRootStore(
    state => state.parameterPointsProgram,
  );

  useScreenViewTracking({
    route,
    title: 'Saiba mais',
  });

  useFocusEffect(
    useCallback(() => {
      if (!hasFocused.current) {
        eventScreenViewV3(
          'saiba_mais',
          'hub_recompensas_spmais',
          'monetizacao',
          {
            location_1: 'monetizacao',
            location_2: 'hub_recompensas_spmais',
            location_3: 'saiba_mais',
          },
        );
        hasFocused.current = true;
      }
      return () => {
        hasFocused.current = false;
      };
    }, []),
  );

  const widthWithPaddingInnerLarger = Math.ceil(width - PADDING_INNER_LARGER);
  const widthWithPaddingInnerLargerWithMargin =
    widthWithPaddingInnerLarger - MARGIN_STANDING_XS;

  const handleNavigation = () => {
    navigation.goBack();
  };

  const items = useMemo((): propsItems[] => {
    if (
      typeof selectedCategory?.value === 'string' ||
      !selectedCategory?.value?.questions ||
      !selectedCategory?.category
    ) {
      return [];
    }

    return selectedCategory.value.questions.map((
      item: {
        question: string;
        answer: string;
      },
      index: number,
    ): propsItems => {
      return {
        id: index,
        title: item.question,
        text: item.answer,
        titleColor: 'BRAND_COMPLEMENT_01',
        headerIconName: (selectedCategory.value as ParameterPointsProgramValue)
          .icon,
        hasSecondaryParagraph: false,
        hideSecondaryIconParagraph: true,
        hideIcon: true,
        onPressCard: () => {
          eventSelectContent({
            content_type: 'cta',
            content_id: sanitizeTaxonomy(item.question),
            location_1: 'monetizacao',
            location_2: 'hub_recompensas_spmais',
            location_3: 'saiba_mais',
          });
        },
      } as propsItems;
    });
  }, [selectedCategory]);

  const hasError =
    !selectedCategory ||
    typeof selectedCategory?.value === 'string' ||
    status === ParameterPointsProgramStatus.ERROR;

  return {
    data: items,
    title: selectedCategory?.category || '',
    widthWithPaddingInnerLargerWithMargin,
    onNavigation: handleNavigation,
    hasError,
  };
}

export default function LearnMoreRewardProgram() {
  const {
    data,
    title,
    widthWithPaddingInnerLargerWithMargin,
    onNavigation,
    hasError,
  } = useLearnMoreRewardProgram();

  if (hasError) {
    return <ApiError onPress={onNavigation} />;
  }

  return (
    <LearnMoreRewardProgramView
      data={data}
      title={title}
      widthWithPaddingInnerLargerWithMargin={
        widthWithPaddingInnerLargerWithMargin
      }
      onNavigation={onNavigation}
    />
  );
}
```

#### **view.tsx (Presentational Component)**
```typescript
import { Box, BoxSafeArea } from '@semparar/design-system-app';
import React from 'react';
import { Platform } from 'react-native';
import FaqContent from '../../atomic/organisms/FaqContent';
import BasicScreen from '../../atomic/templates/BasicScreen';
import { LearnMoreRewardProgramViewProps } from './Models';

const LearnMoreRewardProgramView: React.FC<LearnMoreRewardProgramViewProps> = ({
  data,
  title,
  onNavigation,
}) => {
  return (
    <BasicScreen
      leftIconOnPress={onNavigation}
      title="Saiba mais"
      hasScroll
      bgColor="BRAND_COMPLEMENT_03"
      errorButtonOnPress={onNavigation}
    >
      <BoxSafeArea
        align="flex-start"
        justify="flex-start"
        mode="padding"
        edges={['top']}
      >
        <Box
          mr="xs"
          ml="xs"
          mt={Platform.OS === 'android' ? 'small' : undefined}
        >
          <FaqContent items={data} title={title} />
        </Box>
      </BoxSafeArea>
    </BasicScreen>
  );
};

export default LearnMoreRewardProgramView;
```

#### **Models/index.ts (Type Definitions)**
```typescript
import { propsItems } from '@semparar/design-system-app/src/atomic/organisms/Accordion/Models';

export interface LearnMoreRewardProgramViewProps {
  data: propsItems[];
  title: string;
  widthWithPaddingInnerLargerWithMargin: number;
  onNavigation: () => void;
}

export interface UseLearnMoreRewardProgramReturn {
  data: propsItems[];
  title: string;
  widthWithPaddingInnerLargerWithMargin: number;
  onNavigation: () => void;
  hasError: boolean;
}
```

---

### 3. DESIGN SYSTEM (DS) COMPONENTS IMPORTED

| Component | Source | Purpose |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| `Box` | `@semparar/design-system-app` | Layout container with flex, spacing, colors |
| `BoxSafeArea` | `@semparar/design-system-app` | Safe area layout (handles notches, status bar) |
| `FaqContent` | `../../atomic/organisms/FaqContent` | FAQ/Accordion display for Q&A items |
| `BasicScreen` | `../../atomic/templates/BasicScreen` | Screen template with header, scrolling |
| `ApiError` | `../../atomic/organisms/ApiError` | Error state component |

---

### 4. HOOKS & SERVICES USED

#### **React Navigation Hooks:**
- `useRoute()` - Access route params & metadata
- `useNavigation()` - Navigate between screens
- `useFocusEffect()` - Run side effects on screen focus

#### **React Native Hooks:**
- `useWindowDimensions()` - Get device width/height for responsive sizing
- `useRef()` - Persist flag to track if screen has focused once

#### **Custom Hooks:**
- `useScreenViewTracking()` - Analytics tracking when screen appears

#### **Zustand Store:**
- `useRootStore(state => state.parameterPointsProgram)` - Get:
  - `status` - Loading/Error/Success state
  - `selectedCategory` - Category selected from parent screen (contains questions/answers)
- `useRootStore(state => state.parameterPointsProgramActions)` - Actions (NOT directly used in this screen)

#### **Analytics Functions:**
- `eventScreenViewV3()` - Track screen view event
- `eventSelectContent()` - Track when user clicks accordion item

#### **Utilities:**
- `sanitizeTaxonomy()` - Clean taxonomy strings for analytics

---

### 5. NAVIGATION PARAMS RECEIVED

**Navigation Route:** `LearnMoreRewardProgram`

**Param Type:**
```typescript
type LearnMoreRewardProgramParams = {
  analytics?: {
    screen_name: string;
    screen_class: string;
    screen_bussines: string;
    screen_info: {
      location_1: string;
      location_2: string;
      location_3: string;
    };
  };
};
```

**How Params Are Passed (from LearnMorePointsSection):**
```typescript
navigation.navigate('LearnMoreRewardProgram', {
  analytics: {
    screen_name: 'saiba_mais',
    screen_class: 'hub_recompensas_spmais',
    screen_bussines: 'monetizacao',
    screen_info: {
      location_1: 'monetizacao',
      location_2: 'hub_recompensas_spmais',
      location_3: 'saiba_mais',
    },
  },
});
```

**Note:** The actual data (questions/answers) comes from **Zustand store** (`parameterPointsProgram.selectedCategory`), NOT from navigation params. The screen expects the parent to have:
1. Selected a category via `parameterPointsProgramActions.setSelectedCategory()`
2. Stored the category in the Zustand state

